-- Merkel Rejects Reports on President Wulff Succession, FAZ Says
-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 2012-01-07T14:54:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-07/merkel-rejects-reports-on-president-wulff-succession-faz-says.html
German  Chancellor Angela Merkel  sees
“no reason” to discuss a possible succession of President
 Christian Wulff ,  Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  reported, citing
government spokesman Steffen Seibert.  Rheinische Post  and Frankfurt Allgemeine earlier reported
discussions between Merkel and Vice-Chancellor Philipp Roesler
on how to find a new candidate for the position should Wulff
step down.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  